@node Intro "The short-short introduction..."

Well... ehm... I'm not quite good at writing these things...
Let's try...

@{b}MeMeter@{ub} is a very, very simple, @{"99.9876787578787878%" link Paintium}
systemfriendly program to see how much free memory is left + the
fragmentation of it in a way that makes sense and with a much higher
refreshrate than the the 'numbers in the WB menubar'...

-'s......

It does NOT install itself as a commodity
NO configuration via Tooltypes/Prefs

+'s......

FONT SENSITIVE <-Requested by yODA
The window is resizeable
Pops up on frontmost screen when started
CPU usage is 0.1% on a '020
It won't cause crashes by itself...
@endnode
@node Paintium "LAUGH!!! It's an ORDER!!! :-)"



       ...  Calculated on a Pentium <:*}  ...
@endnode
@node Install

   Ehm...  well... There's only @{b}@{u}1@{ub}@{uu} (one) executable

   so you can't miss it...



   And... there is an installer for the ultimate moron!!!!
@endnode
@node Needs "What it needs..."

   Well, an A1200/060 + 16M + 1.3G HD + 6X CD-ROM + 14" multisync
   won't have any trouble running this 8-}····



   But a plain vanilla A1000 + KS2.0 will be sufficient too...


   It even works with UAE (Unusable Amiga Emulator ;-) ,for those
   PeeCee suckers.....
@endnode
